Rating: 4
This recipe was a big hit in my household. I seasoned a whole chicken lightly with salt, pepper etc before splitting it down the middle and marinating it in the honey mustard sauce. Afetr roasting it for the required amount of time, I put the drippings, some chicken stock and the remaining marinade in a sauce pan, reduced it and added a little cornstarch to thicken. It was fabulous. I can't wait to serve this at a dinner party. Incidentally, bow tie pasta in a slightly sweet vinegarette, green salad and mushrooms sauteed in red wine all go really nicely with this chicken. A keeper for sure.

