Rating: 4
I loved this recipe, however I did do something a little different. I marinated my chicken in all but 3/4 cup of the honey mustard sauce. I then baked it and basted it with my reserve sauce. I chose to make pasta with a jarred alfredo sauce for the side. Towards the end, I had about 1/4-1/2 cup left of the honey mustard sauce left. I tossed it into my alfredo sauce and it was wonderful. The pasta, sauce, and chicken went so well together. It was absolutely delicious.

